{
  "texts": [
    "The objective of the framework is to identify normal and abnormal behavior in the traffic related to the blockchain network.",
    "The classification technique in BChainGuard will be executed locally and the decision function will be embedded as a smart contract.",
    "The results of the experiments are promising, with detection accuracy of approximately 95% using SVM and 98.02% using MLP, and a low runtime with minimal gas consumption overhead.",
    "The weakness of this approach is that it needs to use federated learning in place of machine learning when the dataset is unavailable to help maintain privacy.Kim et al. [34] addressed the privacy, security, and performance issues by introducing a privacy-centric machine learning model for a permissioned blockchain.",
    "The model comprises of an error-based aggregation mechanism and a differentially private stochastic gradient descent algorithm."
  ]
}